@page "/home"
@inject NavigationManager Navigation

<PageTitle>Workspace overview</PageTitle>

<section class="space-y-10">
    <header class="space-y-2">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">
            NexaCRM Server host
        </h1>
        <p class="max-w-3xl text-base text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
            The server project now loads UI assets and components directly from the <code class="rounded bg-slate-200 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm dark:bg-slate-700 dark:text-slate-100">NexaCRM.UI</code>
            Razor class library. Navigation, layouts, and shared resources are sourced from that package to keep the experience identical across hosts.
        </p>
    </header>

    <article class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
        <section class="space-y-4 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/90 p-6 shadow-sm dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900/70">
            <header class="space-y-1">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Unified layout</h2>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
                    Components such as <code class="font-mono text-sm">MainLayout</code>, <code class="font-mono text-sm">NavMenu</code>, and <code class="font-mono text-sm">LoadingScreen</code> are shared from the UI library and consumed by this host.
                </p>
            </header>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
                <p>UI scripts, culture resources, and scoped CSS come from the shared package so both Server and WebAssembly clients stay in sync.</p>
                <p>The router is configured to pick up Razor components from <code class="font-mono text-sm">NexaCRM.UI</code> automatically.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="space-y-4 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/90 p-6 shadow-sm dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900/70">
            <header class="space-y-1">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Supabase ready</h2>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Authentication and data services are wired through shared service abstractions.</p>
            </header>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
                <p>The injected services remain identical regardless of host, so features such as notifications, task tracking, and analytics behave consistently.</p>
                <p>Use this server host to validate Blazor Server specific behaviour while keeping a single source of UI truth.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
    </article>

    <section class="rounded-2xl border border-dashed border-slate-300 bg-white/70 p-6 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900/50 dark:text-slate-300">
        <p>
            Looking for the full application shell? Navigate to <a class="font-medium text-blue-600 underline-offset-4 hover:underline dark:text-blue-400" href="/login">/login</a> to view the NexaCRM experience rendered with components sourced directly from <strong>NexaCRM.UI</strong>.
        </p>
    </section>
</section>

@code {
    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        // /login으로 리다이렉트
        Navigation.NavigateTo("/login", forceLoad: true);
    }
}
